sailpoint.object
Class ProvisioningProject

java.lang.Object
  sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject
      sailpoint.object.ProvisioningProject
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject
public class ProvisioningProject
extends AbstractXmlObject

An object maintaining the state of a complex provisioning process. The project may include one or more plans partitioned for each IntegrationConfig, data gathered interactively for to satisfy templates, and various options.

These are built and updated by the PlanCompiler, and eventually processed by the PlanEvaluator. They can be stored in workflows if approvals are necessary before the plans can be evaluated.

getRoleAssigments

@Deprecated
public java.util.List<RoleAssignment> getRoleAssigments()
Deprecated. replaced by ProvisioningTarget model

The RoleAssignment list was maintained prior to 6.3 to pass information about assigned roles to IIQEvaluator. Starting in 6.3 ProvisioningTarget is used for this, but the property needs to be retained for awhile so plan XML can be parsed in workflows that were created with earlier releases.

getRequester

public java.lang.String getRequester()
Determine who the "requster" of this project is. Remediation plans have historically set this in the "List _requesters" property of the master plan.

Newer plan builders pass the ATT_REQUESTER option in either the master provisioning plan or a compiler option when building the Provisioner.

replace

public boolean replace(ProvisioningPlan orig,
                       ProvisioningPlan neu)
Replace one plan with another. This is intended for use only by PlanEvaluator as it replaces the original plans with the annotated plans returned by the executors.

isEmpty

public boolean isEmpty()
Return true if the project is logically empty. This is an optimization needed by Identitizer which does not want to launch a refresh workflow if there is nothing tangible in the project.

resetCompilation

public void resetCompilation()
Reset the compiled plans. This is intended for use during recompilation where the master plan is recompiled factoring in any newly answered Questions.

The current question list is moved over to the question history list, these will be brought back over if necessary.

getExpansionItem

public ExpansionItem getExpansionItem(ExpansionItem item,
                                      boolean ignoreNullNativeIdentity)
Return a matching ExpansionItem in this project. If ignoreNullNativeIdentity is true, an expansion is returned if everything matches except for a null native identity on the item in the the project. This is used to update existing expansions that might have been added before a native identity was calculated through account selection.

getExpansionItem

public ExpansionItem getExpansionItem(ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest acctReq,
                                      ProvisioningPlan.GenericRequest req,
                                      java.lang.Object value)
Return an ExpansionItem for the given AccountRequest and GenericRequest. Since GenericRequests may contain multiple values, the caller must pass in which value they are concerned with. This returns null if no expansion is found that matches.

getLinkAttribute

public java.lang.Object getLinkAttribute(java.lang.String appName,
                                         java.lang.String nativeIdentity,
                                         java.lang.String instance,
                                         java.lang.String attrName,
                                         ProvisioningPlan.AbstractRequest request,
                                         Identity identity)
Return the requested link attribute value for this identity. This will first try to retrieve a modified value from this project, and if not found will try to get the value from the identity. The operation is checked to be sure that it is not looking for an existing link when performing a create.

If no request is provided, the existing links are checked. If a request is provided, but it is a create, then the existing links are not checked. Providing a null instance or null nativeIdentity will not prevent searching for an existing value on a link.

Parameters:
appName - Name of the Link's application
nativeIdentity - The Link's native identity on the application
instance - Instance that the Link is on. This is often null because instances are optional.
attrName - Name of the attribute that the link corresponds to
request - AccountRequest or ObjectRequest containing the potentially modified Link. If this is null then existing Links will be searched
identity - Identity to which the Link belongs
Returns:
The link attribute value corresponding to the specified criteria

getLinkAttribute

public java.lang.Object getLinkAttribute(java.lang.String appName,
                                         java.lang.String nativeIdentity,
                                         java.lang.String instance,
                                         java.lang.String attrName,
                                         ProvisioningPlan.AbstractRequest request,
                                         Identity identity,
                                         boolean masterOnly)
This is the same as the ProvisioningProject.getLinkAttribute(String, String, String, String, sailpoint.object.ProvisioningPlan.AbstractRequest, Identity) method with the addition of an option to limit the LinkAttribute search to the project's master plan. This is necessary because expansion will sometimes wipe out values that were specified via forms in Custom QuickLinks.

Parameters:
appName - Name of the Link's application
nativeIdentity - The Link's native identity on the application
instance - Instance that the Link is on. This is often null because instances are optional.
attrName - Name of the attribute that the link corresponds to
request - AccountRequest or ObjectRequest containing the potentially modified Link. If this is null then existing Links will be searched
identity - Identity to which the Link belongs
masterOnly - true if the search should be limited to the master plan for the project; false otherwise In most cases this will be false. The search will only be limited to the master plan in cases where expansion may have wiped out a hard-coded value from a custom QuickLink.
Returns:
The link attribute value corresponding to the specified criteria
See Also:
ProvisioningProject.getLinkAttribute(String, String, String, String, sailpoint.object.ProvisioningPlan.AbstractRequest, Identity)
